comment.body:
> Sorry - one last thing, which is off-topic, but I'd like to build some **optional** smarter validation into the `expects` and `promises` macros, maybe around types or expected interfaces vs. the simple validation right now. And once that's done, we can call it a 1.0 release. Obv. @adomokos would need to be on board with this of course. I know he wants to keep things simple and light -- hence the name :)

@gee-forr you might be interested into taking a look at https://github.com/pioneerskies/light_service-validated_context/

Even just to tinkle your ideas reading someone else's code.

> I'm unclear if the localisation gem will be required once it's completely implemented, or if it will remain optional forever?

@gee-forr In my vision it will remain optional; that's why I've thought about implementing a built-in, very simple translation mechanism: offer a sufficient solution without involving further dependencies. That gem would require `i18n` without version constraint as a dependency.

All my vision is a proposal, a reasoning and completely open to discussion.

